#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:806
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 6 - Structure*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:808
msgid "Once the data workflow is in place, the data capture itself can begin."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:810
msgid "In the following slides, we will explore the different types of information that can be captured from specimens or field observations, and see what are the most common mistakes that should be avoided when dealing with each kind of information."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:812
msgid "The main topics will be as follows: taxonomic information, spatial information, collection information, descriptive information."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:814
msgid "Please note that each occurrence (each row in your database or spreadsheet) should have information linked to these 4 main topics in order to be shared and reused accordingly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:815
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide7.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:818
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 7 - Taxonomic information: vocabularies and concepts*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:820
msgid "Taxonomic information is an essential part of the data capture process."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:822
msgid "Without it, a digitized specimen is useless and cannot be properly interpreted or reused."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:824
msgid "Note that the species name is not the only type of taxonomic information that can be exploited in the data capture process: sometimes the specimen hasn’t been identified to the species, and higher taxonomic levels such as the genus or family are still useful for data managers and users."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:825
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide8.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:828
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 8 - Taxonomic information -- be careful with names!*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:830
msgid "Most of the time, the scientific name is the main way of retrieving data in a database, portal, website, browser, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:832
msgid "Any error in the spelling or authority can lead to wrong or null queries, thus impeding the management and potential reuse of the data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:834
msgid "This is why it’s very important to check all categories of scientific names to fix errors and/or omissions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:835
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide9.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:838
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 9 - Taxonomic information: common mistakes to avoid*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:840
msgid "The most common issues occurring with taxon information are missing or inconsistent information, incorrect or non-atomic values, duplicates and uncertainty."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:842
msgid "Always check the definitions and examples of taxonomic Darwin Core terms to avoid nomenclatural mistakes: http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/index.htm"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:843
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide10.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:846
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 10 - Spatial information: vocabulary and concepts*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:848
msgid "Geographic information proves to be valuable in a lot of data re-use contexts, such as niche modelling or studies about species distribution."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:850
msgid "While ‘old’ collections or specimens can be understandably difficult, if not impossible, to geolocate precisely, it is recommended to share precise coordinates or textual information when possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:853
msgid "Coordinates should be recorded directly on the field when possible, along with the uncertainty and the geodetic datum used.  Otherwise use relevant and verified sources to geolocate your data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:855
msgid "You should note that coordinates or other geographic information can be generalized or not even shared at all in some contexts, such as with the conservation of sensitive species."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:856
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide11.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:859
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 11 - Spatial information: what are we talking about?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:861
msgid "Spatial information can be found in numerous formats, not only geographic coordinates: examples include (but are not limited to) grid data, point+radius, or polygons."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:863
msgid "Each of them is useful to share in order to check the consistency of the geographical elements (for example coordinates vs country code, or to ensure a given locality is consistent with a collector’s travels)"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:865
msgid "Point+radius image: https://live.staticflickr.com/5820/23736048306_35dfd89c05_b.jpg"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:866
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide12.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:869
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 12 - Spatial information: a few more definitions*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:871
msgid "Within GBIF, it is recommended to share the geodetic Datum that was used to derive the coordinates that were shared (decimal latitude and longitude)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:873
msgid "In the absence of a specific geodetic datum, GBIF will infer WGS84 as default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:874
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide13.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:877
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 13 - Spatial information: common mistakes to avoid*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:879
msgid "This slide shows an old GBIF map with different types of geographical issues: the most obvious one is a mirror effect between the USA and China (reversed coordinates),"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:882
msgid "You can also notice an artificial line along the Greenwich meridian where ‘0’ values were put in the ‘decimalLongitude’ field, as well as another one on the Equator where ‘0’ values were put in the ‘decimalLatitude’ field."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:885
msgid "GBIF indexing now includes automatic geographical checks between the coordinates and countryCode shared within the dataset.  Coordinates can be automatically reversed to match the country."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:886
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide14.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:889
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 14 - Collection information: vocabularies and concepts*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:891
msgid "Information about the context of the data collection or observation are very useful to share in order to give as much detail as possible regarding each occurrence."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:893
msgid "Information such as the collector name, collection or observation protocol, habitat and other factors can prove to be important when reusing data for example with ecological niche modelling."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:895
msgid "Depending on the dataset type, other information might also become relevant."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:897
msgid "Image credit: https://pixabay.com/fr/photos/tige-afrique-jumelles-bush-safari-863823/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:898
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide15.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:901
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 15 - Collection information: things to keep in mind*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:903
msgid "Data quality factors regarding collection information are mainly along the lines of exactitude like the correct collector name, consistency for example using the same vocabulary for describing soils, habitats, and completeness as in providing all existing information about the description of a given species including the flowering period, colour of the leaves, and medicinal uses."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:906
#, no-wrap
msgid "Within the Darwin Core and within the IPT you can find recommended controlled vocabularies for some fields such as the ‘lifeStage’.\n"
" The TDWG vocabularies task group works to promote and make better the ease of use across vocabularies.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:907
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide16.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:910
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 16 - Descriptive information: vocabularies and concepts*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:912
msgid "Keep in mind that descriptive information are often incomplete due to a whole array of factors."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:916
msgid "Depending on the collection state, some labels can be incomplete or lacking crucial information; Completeness (for example of a species description) is often impossible to achieve with a single individual; and you should always check for consistency in your database or spreadsheet, for example in the terms used for describing colours, in order to avoid redundant information."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:918
msgid "Image credit: Dataset Taiwan Moth Occurrence Data Collected From Social Network"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:920
msgid "https://api.gbif.org/v1/image/unsafe/http%3A%2F%2Fmothimage.mauchiuan.com%2F%2Fimages%2Ftwmoth006%2Ftwmoth028104.jpg"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:921
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide17.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:924
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 17 - Summary*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:926
msgid "This presentation has focused on the topic of data quality applied to data capture; indeed, these are the steps where it is crucial to ensure that all information related to each record is correctly and completely captured, in order for the data to be as clear and understandable as possible for future users."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:928
msgid "This can only be done if consistent decisions are made at the institutional level in order to create a solid workflow for data capture and data management."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:930
msgid "The chain of responsibility regarding data quality is then split between the persons involved at each step of the process, but keep in mind that data can always be improved and fixed if errors or omissions are detected at later stages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:931
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::capture-quality-Slide18.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/capture.adoc:934
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 18 - Conclusion*\n"
msgstr ""

